<DIV dir=ltr align=left><SPAN class=329503520-12022010><FONT face=Arial 
color=#0000ff size=2>The proto for tm_init looks like this:</FONT></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV dir=ltr align=left><SPAN class=329503520-12022010><FONT face=Arial 
color=#0000ff size=2>int tm_init(void *info, struct tm_roots 
*roots);</FONT></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV dir=ltr align=left><SPAN class=329503520-12022010><FONT face=Arial 
color=#0000ff size=2></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV dir=ltr align=left><SPAN class=329503520-12022010><FONT face=Arial 
color=#0000ff size=2>where the struct has 6 elements: 2&nbsp;x tm_task_id + 3 x 
int + 1 x tm_task_id</FONT></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV dir=ltr align=left><SPAN class=329503520-12022010><FONT face=Arial 
color=#0000ff size=2></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV dir=ltr align=left><SPAN class=329503520-12022010><FONT face=Arial 
color=#0000ff size=2>If the API was different, wouldn't the compiler most likely 
generate an error at compile-time?</FONT></SPAN></DIV>
